President Obama will be delivering his annual Back-to-School Speech on September 28th, 2011, at Benjamin Banneker Academic High School in Washington, DC. The event is open to pre-credentialed media only and is by invitation. The speech is an opportunity for the President to directly address students and encourage them to study hard, take responsibility for their education, and set goals for themselves. Benjamin Banneker Academic High School is a magnet school known for its rigorous academic programs and high graduation rates. The speech will be live-streamed on WhiteHouse.gov for classrooms across the country to watch, and it will also be featured on MSNBC as part of NBC News' "Education Nation" programming.